               The ſoule of man, ſo long as it is in bondage vnto the bodie, it ſeeketh onelie the bodies pleaſures and delights, but hauing once recouered that ſeruitude, and brought the bodie to be ſubiect vnto it, then it ſeeketh no longer, the peace, pleaſure, eaſe and reſt of the bodie, but now being freed from that bondage, and reſtored to it ſelfe, it ſeeketh it owne peace, reſt, health, and happines for euer.  S. 99. P. 44. &amp; 45.
